modules.description: Parses Content-Type values according to RFC822 and RFC2045, extracting media types, parameters, and subtypes. It processes strings and structured data representing MIME types, including handling IANA-registered values. Used to accurately interpret HTTP headers, email headers, and other protocol fields requiring strict content type validation.

Provides functions to parse, format, and compare content types with media type, subtype, and parameter values. Works with types representing media types, subtypes, parameter values, and full content structures. Used to validate and serialize HTTP content types, ensuring correct handling of MIME headers in network protocols.
